  "elapsed_s": 74.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Nobody was interested and eager until we became a political nuisance over a few years that we finally began to make our-- our-- our way.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Now I myself, I had left Feldafing probably sometime in August or September and wanted to make my way to Switzerland because I knew that Switzerland was the one country that was intact, and there were American representatives there.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And I could begin to look for a way of getting to America.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But to get to Switzerland, ultimately-- and I'm really trying to be as brief about this as I can-- I-- I had to swim over the Rhine in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And after a private arrangement with someone from Switzerland, I was taken to Zurich and then had to hide for it must be about three, four months in Switzerland, where there was still rationing, and where, you know, it wasn't easy to manipulate illegally.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Hiding and being driven from one place to another, and eventually when I needed to get a-- a transit visa to-- through France in order to get to Belgium, to Antwerp, to get on a boat, I was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I had a letter from the American consulate in-- in Zurich that they were ready to give me a visa.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And because it was addressed to someone, one of the Jewish families in Zurich, the man who, when the letter was received, cut out his address, so he wouldn't be caught.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And then I had folded it over, and the French consul opened it up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And he saw the hole, so he told me that he had to go and consult somebody.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And when I-- and I of course immediately realized that he sensed something fishy.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
